==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Judicatory
<hw>Ju"di*ca*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>judicatorius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the administration of
justice; dispensing justice; judicial; <as>as, <ex>judicatory</ex>
tribunals</as>.</def> <rj><au>T. Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Power to reject in an authoritative or <qex>judicatory</qex>
way.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Judicatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Judicatory
